List of ansible modules used in regular

ansible command line options: 
------------------------------
$ ansible -m --> module
          -a --> module arguments
          -i --> inventory file
          -e --> extra-vars
          -u --> remote_user
          -s --> sudo 
          -b --> become
          --become-methord --> sudo | su | pbrun | pfexec | doas | dzdo | ksu | runas | pmrun | enable | machinectl

1. ping / ansible.builtin.ping
2. command / ansible.builtin.command
3. shell / ansible.builtin.shell
4. debug / ansible.builtin.debug --> to print any msg during the exicution
5. 


Playbook keywords:
-------------------
hosts: 
tasks:
gather_facts: false/true
become: yes
vars:
   ansible_become_user:
